# Section 0: CLI Runner Contract

This prompt is designed to run as a CLI under a future
`agent.code_reviewer.frontend` Python entry point. The runner module is
**MISSING_TODAY** (`agent/code_reviewer/frontend/__main__.py` does not yet
exist) — the section below is the spec the runner will conform to. Until the
runner ships, the prompt is invoked manually and the `ReviewReport` JSON
(Section 8) is hand-written by the agent.

## Invocation

```
python -m agent.code_reviewer.frontend \
    --files <comma_separated_paths_or_globs> \
    --scope <full|adapter_pr|ui_component_pr|wire_translator_pr|security_audit|sprint_audit|infra_audit> \
    --out <path/to/review.json> \
    [--fail-on <critical|warning|none>]
```

- `--files` accepts a comma-separated list of paths or glob patterns
  (e.g. `frontend/lib/adapters/**/*.ts,frontend/components/chat/Composer.tsx`).
  When omitted, defaults to `git diff --name-only --diff-filter=ACMR origin/main...HEAD`.
- `--scope` selects which dimensions to evaluate. See Section 3 for the
  dimension catalogue (FD1-FD11) and `review_submission.j2` for the named
  scope → dimension mapping. Defaults to `full`.
- `--out` is the destination path for the structured `ReviewReport` JSON
  object (Section 8). Required. Pass `-` to emit JSON to stdout instead;
  in that case the human-readable `statement` is written to stderr.
- `--fail-on` decides the process exit code derived from the verdict.
  Defaults to `critical` (CI-friendly).

## Stdin / Stdout / Stderr

- The runner reads file contents from disk; nothing is piped through stdin.
- Stdout is reserved for the human-readable `statement` field (one paragraph).
  All structured data goes to `--out`.
- Stderr carries diagnostic logs (tool invocation traces, classification
  decisions, judge-gate kills) — never findings.

## Exit Codes

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `0` | `verdict == "approve"` (or verdict is below the `--fail-on` threshold). |
| `1` | `verdict == "request_changes"` (or any warning when `--fail-on warning`). |
| `2` | `verdict == "reject"` (always non-zero, regardless of `--fail-on`). |
| `3` | Runner error (tool crash, unparseable file, missing baseline, prompt did not produce valid JSON). Distinct from `2` so CI can separate "reviewer is broken" from "reviewer found problems". |

`--fail-on critical` exits non-zero only when the verdict is
`request_changes` or `reject`. `--fail-on warning` exits non-zero on any
warning-or-worse finding even when the overall verdict is `approve`.
`--fail-on none` always exits `0` (advisory-only runs).

## Output Path Contract

The full `ReviewReport` JSON (Section 8) is the source of truth. The
`statement` field on stdout is a UX convenience and must NEVER be parsed by
downstream tooling — diff, gate, or annotate from the JSON only.

