# Section 3: Validation Dimensions (FD1-FD7)

## FD1: Layering & Dependency Direction
**Rules covered:** F1-F4, the §10 import tables (Browser+BFF + Middleware sub-rings), F-R1..F-R5.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic AST tools (`classify_frontend_layer`, `parse_ts_imports`, `check_frontend_dependency_rules`).
**Severity:** CRITICAL for any dependency violation.

## FD2: Pattern Adherence
**Rules covered:** W1-W8, P1-P7, A1-A10, T1-T4, X1-X6, C1-C5, B1-B7, U1-U8, S1-S3, O1-O4, F-R6/F-R7/F-R8.
**Evidence source:** Mixed. AST/shell tools for the deterministic majority; LLM judgment for B6 (Route Handler business logic) and U1 ("should this be RSC?").
**Severity:** WARNING for pattern deviations, INFO for style suggestions.

## FD3: Security & Sandboxing
**Rules covered:** §15 iframe sandbox, §19 strict CSP nonce strategy, §16 sealed envelope, F-R9 BFF credentials boundary, OWASP additions (`NEXT_PUBLIC_*` secrets, JWT storage, `productionBrowserSourceMaps`, `images.remotePatterns`, security headers).
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (`check_csp_strict`, `check_iframe_sandbox`, `check_secrets_in_public_env`, `check_jwt_storage`, file reads of `next.config.ts` and `middleware.ts`).
**Severity:** CRITICAL on the auto-reject hypotheses (see Section 8); WARNING otherwise.

## FD4: Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA)
**Rules covered:** U4 ARIA live region, U5 focus management, §13 a11y rules; auto-checkable subset via axe-core and `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y`.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (`check_axe_a11y`, `run_eslint_jsx_a11y`) for the auto-checkable subset; appropriateness/announcement-fatigue/focus-orientation marked as `gaps` (never as findings -- see Section 9, Anti-Pattern Guard #6).
**Severity:** WARNING; CRITICAL on serious axe rules (impact `critical` or `serious`).

## FD5: Performance & Streaming
**Rules covered:** §18 bundle policy (10% regression gate), X5 backpressure, X6 SSE header invariants, B5 `cache: 'no-store'` default, B6 Route Handler hygiene, image optimization, code splitting.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (`check_bundle_budget`, AST scans for `cache: 'force-cache'`, `<img>`, `Content-Encoding: gzip` on stream routes, missing SSE headers).
**Severity:** WARNING; INFO for soft hints (e.g., suggested `next/dynamic` candidates).

## FD6: Tests & Architecture Tests
**Rules covered:** §20 testing pyramid; port conformance test presence (P7); `tests/architecture/test_frontend_layering.ts` presence; wire schema drift baseline (W2); Storybook coverage for generative-UI components; failure-paths-first for adapter tests; `tsc --noEmit` clean.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (`check_port_conformance`, `check_wire_drift`, `check_storybook_coverage`, `run_tsc_strict`, file system checks).
**Severity:** WARNING for missing required test, INFO for coverage suggestions.

## FD7: Anti-Patterns
**Rules covered:** FE-AP-1 through FE-AP-20.
**Evidence source:** Mixed. Most are AST-detectable via `detect_frontend_anti_patterns` and the family-specific tools; the rest are LLM-judged (e.g., FE-AP-1 "god utility" requires reading the module).
**Severity:** Per-AP severity table in Section 8.

## FD8: Sprint Story Alignment
**Rules covered:** Sprint board acceptance criteria for stories `S0.1.1` through `S4.3.2` (`docs/plan/frontend/SPRINT_BOARD.md`). The authoritative per-story `key_files`, `acceptance_signal`, and cached `known_status` columns live in the `Sprint Story Acceptance Map` section of `architecture_rules.j2`.
**Evidence source:** Re-derive on every run via `check_sprint_story` (file-system inspection of `key_files` + dispatch to the `acceptance_signal` shell command). Never trust the cached `known_status` column verbatim — it is a hint to seed hypotheses, not a finding.
**Severity:** WARNING for `PARTIAL`; INFO for `FAIL` when the gap is documented as accepted (operational items deferred to Sprint 4, the Spike B/D skip per Decisions D-S0-5/D-S0-6, the Spike C latency debt per D-S0-8); CRITICAL only for stories whose cross-cutting DoD row maps to an existing FD1-FD3 auto-reject hypothesis (`FE-AP-4`/`-6`/`-7`/`-12`/`-18`/`-19` or `CSP1`/`CSP2`/`SBX2`/`SEC1`/`SEC2`/`TRUST1`/`TRUST2`). FD8 itself adds no new auto-rejects.

## FD9: Middleware Ring (Python)
**Rules covered:** `M1`, `F1`, `F4`, `M-ports`, `M-no-cross`, `A2` mirrored verbatim from `tests/architecture/test_middleware_layer.py`. Concretely: `middleware/server.py` does not Python-import `orchestration/` (graph loaded via `langgraph.json` config string reference); `middleware/composition.py` is the sole reader of `ARCHITECTURE_PROFILE`; `middleware/ports/*` import only stdlib + Pydantic + `agent_ui_adapter/wire/` + `trust/`; `middleware/adapters/{auth,acl,memory,observability}/*` confine the SDK packages `jwt`, `mem0ai`, `langfuse`, `workos` and never import sibling adapter families.
