## Verdict Decision Rules (strictest)

**Auto-reject (the verdict MUST be `reject` if ANY of these conditions hold; the offending rule IDs appear inline at the top of `statement`):**

- Any critical finding in **FD1** (Layering & Dependency Direction).
- Any critical finding in **FD9** (Middleware Ring) — the `tests/architecture/test_middleware_layer.py` failures are equivalent in severity to FD1 because they enforce the same layering arrow on the Python side.
- Any of the following anti-patterns confirmed:
  - **FE-AP-4** -- `useComponent` iframe without `sandbox` (security-critical XSS surface).
  - **FE-AP-6** -- mutating a sealed envelope (breaks trust-gate signature verification).
  - **FE-AP-7** -- generating `trace_id` in the browser (breaks F-R7 trust propagation).
  - **FE-AP-12** -- `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` of agent output (XSS vector).
  - **FE-AP-18** -- BFF holds a cloud credential (F-R9 violation).
  - **FE-AP-19** -- adding `'unsafe-inline'` to CSP (defeats nonce strategy).
- Any critical FD3 finding from these specific hypotheses:
  - `FD3.CSP1` -- CSP includes `'unsafe-inline'` or `'unsafe-eval'`.
  - `FD3.CSP2` -- CSP missing nonce + `'strict-dynamic'`.
  - `FD3.SBX2` -- iframe `sandbox` includes a dangerous token.
  - `FD3.SEC1` -- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` secret leak.
  - `FD3.SEC2` -- JWT in `localStorage`/`sessionStorage`.
  - `FD3.TRUST1` -- sealed envelope spread/re-serialized.
  - `FD3.TRUST2` -- browser-side `trace_id` generation.

**FD8, FD10, and FD11 add NO new auto-reject conditions.** They inherit auto-rejects only when their hypotheses overlap an existing FD1/FD3 rule (e.g. `FD10.CF_PAGES_ENV` inherits `FD3.SEC1` / `FE-AP-18`; `FD10.SM_NAMING` inherits the same). A pure FD8 PARTIAL story, an FD10 missing `startup_cpu_boost`, or an FD11 missing `monitoring.tf` is at most WARNING (or INFO when it is a documented operational gap).

**Otherwise:**
- **request_changes:** any other critical finding OR more than 2 warnings.
- **approve:** 0 critical findings AND ≤2 warnings.

The `statement` field MUST begin with the verdict, then list every auto-reject reason by rule ID before any other commentary.

